Nigerian journalist, Kemi Olunloyo, has taken to social media to air her opinion, following the counsel of pastor Becky Enenche to Nigerian parents that they should never consider divorce in their marriages.
Recall that Nigerian gospel singer, Osinachi Nwachukwu, was reported dead at an Abuja hospital few days ago, following the abuse and beatings she received from her husband, Peter Nwachukwu.
However, following such unfortunate incident, an old tweet of pastor Becky Enenche resurfaced online, where the clergywoman advised Nigerian parents to never make divorce an option because it might affect the their children in the future.
The clergywoman also revealed that most wayward and rough children are products of divorced homes.
Here is Becky Enenche’s tweet below;
However, following Becky Enenche’s counsel to parents, Nigerian journalist, Kemi Olunloyo, took to her official Twitter account to react, as she stated that there is nothing wrong with the advise of pastor Becky Enenche to Nigerian parents.
Kemi Olunloyo went ahead to reveal that most children from divorced homes are drug addicts, adding that Nigerians should be very careful when they want to get married.
Kemi Olunloyo finally disclosed that many children from single homes also succeed in life.
